antum", "level": 3, "id": "HGL61", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h4", "text": "A. NUMBER", "level": 4, "id": "HGL62", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 1: The Species of Calculation in Arithmetic; Kant's Synthetic Propositions  a priori  of Intuition", "level": 6, "id": "HGL63", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 2: The Employment of Numerical Distinctions for Expressing Philosophical Notions", "level": 6, "id": "HGL64", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h4", "text": "B. EXTENSIVE AND INTENSIVE QUANTUM", "level": 4, "id": "HGL65", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(a) Their Difference", "level": 5, "id": "HGL66", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(b) Identity of Extensive and Intensive Magnitude", "level": 5, "id": "HGL67", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 1: Examples of This Identity", "level": 6, "id": "HGL68", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 2: The determination of degree as applied by Kant to the soul", "level": 6, "id": "HGL69", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(c) Alteration of Quantum", "level": 5, "id": "HGL610", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h4", "text": "C. QUANTITATIVE INFINITY", "level": 4, "id": "HGL611", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(a) Its Notion", "level": 5, "id": "HGL612", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(b) The Quantitative Infinite Progress", "level": 5, "id": "HGL613", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 1: The High Repute of the Progress to Infinity", "level": 6, "id": "HGL614", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 2: The Kantian Antinomy of the Limitation and Non-limitation of the World in Time and Space", "level": 6, "id": "HGL615", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "(c) The Infinity of Quantum", "level": 5, "id": "HGL616", "filename": "HGSL6.html"}, {"tag": "h6", "text": "Remark 1: The Specific